==English==

===Pronunciation===
*shēth, /ʃiːθ/, /<tt>Si:T</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːθ|Rhymes: -iːθ]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[scēaþ]]''
===Noun===
'''sheath''' (pl. ''[[sheaths]]'')

#A [[scabbard]]; a [[holster]] for a [[sword]].
#Anything that has a similar shape to a scabbard for a sword that is for the purpose of holding an object that is [[long]]er than it is [[wide]]; a [[case]].  
#A [[tight-fitting]] [[dress]].

====Synonyms====
*(''scabbard''): [[scabbard]]
*(''long case''): [[case]], [[casing]], [[cover]], [[covering]], [[envelope]]
*(''tight-fitting dress''):

====Related terms====
*[[sheathe]]
*[[heliosheath]]
*[[resheath]], [[resheathe]]
*[[unsheath]], [[unsheathe]]

